HEADWORD: Mahoe
<hw>Ma"hoe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to several malvaceous trees (species of <gen>Hibiscus</gen>,
<gen>Ochroma</gen>, etc.), and to their strong fibrous inner bark, which
is used for strings and cordage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

